== Objective
The objective of this test is to ensure the MPHX jig's ability to reliably move through the feed and roller systems without the risk of catching at any point in the system. The main concern is that the the button head screws that hold the shim stock may catch along gaps in the feed or the countersunk feed mounting holes due to the sliding motion. By procedurally conducting dry runs and tallying the times and locations of catching, we can identify and mitigate the most likely causes of failure.

